# Documentation Standards

## File Organization

- `docs/` — guides, standards, reference docs
- `docs/plans/` — implementation plans (named `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md`)
- Generated docs (`icon-inventory.md`, `components.md`) are auto-built via `cd ui && npm run docs`

## Formatting

- Every doc must start with YAML frontmatter (`---` delimiters)
- Use ATX headings (`#`, `##`, `###`) — no setext underlines
- Cross-reference other docs with relative links (e.g., `[design strategy](design-strategy.md)`)
- Code examples must specify language in fenced blocks

## Content Rules

- Standards docs are the "constitution" — agent rules and cursor rules point to them
- Keep docs concise and actionable, not verbose
- Update `AGENTS.md` or cursor rules when adding a new standard doc
- Never include real API keys, credentials, or personal data in examples
